<br>
On the points on Iran,<br>
1. While intact, most of it's aircraft are old and out of date. Mig 29's are not the match of an F-15 or F-14 in combat and would lose badly with such low numbers. US pilots are also better trained, and training counts. (By the way the Su-35 is the most up to date Russian air superiority fighter)<br>
<br>
2. It is true that their defense network is intact but there are a number of ways of taking down SAM networks, extensive jamming and anti-radiation missiles make an effective combination. It would likely take a few weeks to eliminate most of the network, but mobile systems could be hid for nasty surprises later.<br>
<br>
3. This is true, we do not have unlimited stocks, and would not be able to mount an extensive campaign.<br>
<br>
4. The submarines (particularly the newer Kilo's) are probably the greatest threat listed here. Anti-ship missiles are easier to deal with.<br>
<br>
5. I don't see this strategy working. Carriers are sitting ducks all alone, which is why they are constantly protected by aircraft, warships and submarines. The formidible Coalition air defenses and their multiphasic radars would take mere seconds to come into action and would swamp an incomming attack with hundreds if not thousands of SAMs (the long-range Standard launches on US cruisers and destroyers take 3-4 seconds to reload between shots). The layered air defenses would rip Iran's aircraft and anti-ship missiles to pieces. The best use of the subs would be to sink toop and cargo transports, big impact targets which are less heavily defended then carriers. <p>&quot;If,&quot; he wispered, &quot;if we could only pick that lock....&quot; - , THE WORLD SET FREE</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=timberwind@nuclearspace>timberwind</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Space Cadet</span><br>  Posts: 43<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(4/1/03 7:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=405.topic&index=51>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: We are winning!</span><hr size=1> Discovery 1,<br>
